seits die herrschenden gesellschaftlichen Genderkonstrukte reflektiert und andererseits neue Konzepte oder gar Utopien entwirft, widmet sich der Band einem aktuellen Thema, das über kulturwissenschaftliche Fragen hinausweist.  aThis volume is the first to diachronously present the development of gender in German children's and young-adult literature from the middle ages to the present. It explores a topic of enormous societal relevance by examining books that have accompanied the socialization of young people on a spectrum between dominant discourses and utopian visions.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mai 2023) 0aChildrenxBooks and readingzGermany. 0aSex role in childrenzGermany. 0aSex role in literature. 4aGender. 4aKinder- und Jugendliteratur. 4aLiteraturgeschichte. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Children's & Young Adult Literature.2bisacsh  aChildren's and young-adult literature.  agender theory.  aliterary history.1 aBackes, Martina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBernstorff, Wiebke von, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBlumesberger, Susanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFlüh, Marie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeigel, Christian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHoppe, Henriette, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHorstmann, Jan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJessen, Jennifer, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKebe-Nguema, Joseph